		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />3D objects have been done on the NES, though only in wire frame - see the game "Elite", as well as "Tank Demo" (same author).
<br />
<br />Texture mapping, however, is almost certainly out of the question, as it would require far too much CPU time and PPU bandwidth to be feasible.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
