	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tokumaru</b> [ Tue Feb 14, 2006 10:08 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />lord_Chile, I barelly understood what you said. It has nothing to do with the topic, but each name table is 960 (32*30) bytes long. Right after is the attributte table for that name table, and it's 64 (8*8) bytes long. Each name table + attribute table pair is 1024 (960 + 64) bytes, or 1kb long. The NES has 2kb of VRAM, so we get 2 name tables and 2 attribute tables. If that's what you were asking.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


